700118f-c.text:

700119f-a.title: Bronx: 146th Street - Gerard Avenue
700119f-a.text:
(1)
East 146th Street, at the S.E. corner of Gerard Ave., showing the Stephens House. Stephens lived here from 1869 to 1893 when he bought the Francis House, at the N.E. corner of the aforementioned street. For additional data see "Gas Logic", February 1933 and the
New York Times February 2, 1935.
November 29, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.

The same, another view.
